{"questionId":"26531","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The strength of earthquakes is measured on the Richter magnitude scale, with values&nbsp;typically between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;is the most severe.</p>\n<p>The Gutenberg–Richter equation gives the average number of earthquakes per year,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi></math>,&nbsp;which have a magnitude of at least&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>. For a particular region the equation is</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi></math>, for some&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>This region has an average of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn></math>&nbsp;earthquakes per year with a magnitude of at least&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The equation for this region can also be written as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><msup><mn>10</mn><mi>M</mi></msup></mfrac></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Within this region the most severe earthquake recorded had a magnitude of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the average number of earthquakes in a year with a magnitude of at least <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00631</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0063095</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept an answer of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26531","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ1.12c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the average number of earthquakes in a year with a magnitude of at least 7.2.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.5—Intro to logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}